Rating: 4
Wonderful recipe, however I can't believe I am saying this as my husband and I are the ultimate lime freaks--we thought the lime taste was a bit overpowering. Next time we might not use zest, just the juice. Anyway, this tart was fairly simple to make, looked gorgeous and tasted delicious; this shaped tart pan is so pretty and less predictable than round ones are. The raspberry sauce/juice stuff you cook on the stove never got solid and I am not sure it is supposed to, but that could be my fault as I let it boil wildly (cause I forgot about it) but it didn't matter; it creates only a very thin layer anyway and is delicious. This dessert is a real winner.

